record.title: Christian church architecture
record.detail: Church architecture in Sydney has at times been the most significant and exceptional in the architecture of Sydney. At other times, church denominations have settled on continuing a successful type, seeking to make a noticeable character across the region. As immigrants imported their traditions, they adapted to the materials and surroundings of the new country.

record.title: church
record.detail: The Ebenezer Church was built by a group of Hawkesbury settlers of various denominations who came together for Sunday services. Designed by Andrew Johnston, a member of the congregation, it was built of local materials, sandstone, cedar and hardwood. In 2010 an extensive five-year restoration project won a New South Wales Heritage Branch Award.
